"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-sport-othersport-2047409-sadiq-khan-london-olympic-games-2040\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  Sadiq Khanhas backedLondonto bid for the 2040 Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 62, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2, \"end\": 7, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sadiq_Nawaz\", \"score\": 0.9953214769665063, \"rank\": 0.004700514475663585, \"text\": \"Sadiq\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sadiq_Nawaz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sadiq_Nawaz\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A campaign launched by the Mayor of London is pushing for the capital to become the first city in the world to host the Summer Olympics on four separate occasions.\", \"from\": 63, \"to\": 226, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 99, \"end\": 105, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.999982860838366, \"rank\": 1.6979229183829996e-05, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"London last hosted the multi-sport spectacle in 2012, when billions of pounds was pumped into constructing the Queen Elizabeth Olympic Park in Stratford, which included brand new state-of-the-art venues like the London Stadium, the Aquatics Centre and the Velodrome.\", \"from\": 228, \"to\": 494, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 228, \"end\": 234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.999982860838366, \"rank\": 1.6979229183829996e-05, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 371, \"end\": 380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stratford-upon-Avon\", \"score\": 0.9662635968023612, \"rank\": 0.03451501841349049, \"text\": \"Stratford\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stratford-upon-Avon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stratford-upon-Avon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Khan's campaign involves using those facilities to bring the Games back to Great Britain as part of a wider strategy aimed at making London 'the sporting capital of the world'.\", \"from\": 495, \"to\": 671, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 495, \"end\": 499, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shah_Rukh_Khan\", \"score\": 0.9985076026229774, \"rank\": 0.0013827963822597676, \"text\": \"Khan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q33999\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shah_Rukh_Khan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shah_Rukh_Khan\"}, {\"begin\": 570, \"end\": 583, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9139837252453228, \"rank\": 0.09404150786420488, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He toldThe Times: \\\"My ambition has always been for London to be the sporting capital of the world, and then to consolidate our position.\", \"from\": 673, \"to\": 809, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 724, \"end\": 730, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.999982860838366, \"rank\": 1.6979229183829996e-05, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I would like to see London become the first city to host the Games four times.\", \"from\": 810, \"to\": 888, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 830, \"end\": 836, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.999982860838366, \"rank\": 1.6979229183829996e-05, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Globally, everyone loves coming to London.\", \"from\": 890, \"to\": 933, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 926, \"end\": 932, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.999982860838366, \"rank\": 1.6979229183829996e-05, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And we have managed to stage a good event every year in the London Diamond League.\", \"from\": 934, \"to\": 1016, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 994, \"end\": 1000, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.999982860838366, \"rank\": 1.6979229183829996e-05, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 1001, \"end\": 1015, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2017_Diamond_League\", \"score\": 0.9964908597617315, \"rank\": 0.0035214969913874286, \"text\": \"Diamond League\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2017_Diamond_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2017_Diamond_League\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I was in Paris last summer and I saw the transformation of their city.\", \"from\": 1017, \"to\": 1087, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1026, \"end\": 1031, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999437579861, \"rank\": 5.624209224436527e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But we could knock it out of the park in relation to the Olympics, using the assets we already have in the aquatics centre, the stadium, the velodrome.\", \"from\": 1089, \"to\": 1241, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And we could have some events outside of London too.\", \"from\": 1242, \"to\": 1294, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1283, \"end\": 1289, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.999982860838366, \"rank\": 1.6979229183829996e-05, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"When it comes to major sports events, the public and governments are not unreasonably nervous about a huge amount of money being spent on infrastructure.\", \"from\": 1298, \"to\": 1452, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But the reason why 2040 makes sense for London is because we could do it in a brilliant way but also very cheaply.\", \"from\": 1453, \"to\": 1567, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1493, \"end\": 1499, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.999982860838366, \"rank\": 1.6979229183829996e-05, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An Olympics in London would not cost a fortune, but the benefits would be humongous.\\\"\", \"from\": 1568, \"to\": 1653, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1583, \"end\": 1589, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.999982860838366, \"rank\": 1.6979229183829996e-05, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Mayor of London's office is publishing a report to outline the financial benefits which arose from hosting six significant sporting events last year.\", \"from\": 1655, \"to\": 1808, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1668, \"end\": 1674, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.999982860838366, \"rank\": 1.6979229183829996e-05, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Champions League final and regular-season NFL games, among other events, are said to have generated \\u00a3230million for the economy and brought in hundreds and thousands of spectators.\", \"from\": 1809, \"to\": 1993, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1855, \"end\": 1858, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Football_League\", \"score\": 0.929265285467033, \"rank\": 0.070935475895701, \"text\": \"NFL\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Football_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Football_League\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We use your sign-up to provide content in ways you have consented to and to improve our understanding of you.\", \"from\": 1995, \"to\": 2104, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This may include adverts from us and 3rd parties based on our understanding.\", \"from\": 2105, \"to\": 2181, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can unsubscribe at any time.\", \"from\": 2182, \"to\": 2214, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy Policy  Khan says the previous government 'had no interest in the importance of bringing sport to our country', and he is working with the current government on a bid for 2029 World Athletics Championship, which could be worth \\u00a3400m to London.\", \"from\": 2215, \"to\": 2474, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2467, \"end\": 2473, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.999982860838366, \"rank\": 1.6979229183829996e-05, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He added: \\\"If we have the World Championships in 2029, it means in the lead-up [to the Games in 2040] there is energy, enthusiasm and investment in track and field, which means you will have the future Mo Farahs, the future Paula Radcliffes.\\\"\", \"from\": 2476, \"to